# Volatility Forecasting Engine & Risk Analytics Dashboard

An end-to-end quantitative finance project for volatility forecasting and market risk analysis.

The project implements multiple volatility models, evaluates forecasting performance, estimates Value at Risk (VaR), performs backtesting, and provides an interactive Streamlit dashboard for model comparison and risk visualization.

---

# Project Overview

Volatility is one of the most important concepts in quantitative finance, affecting:

- portfolio risk management
- derivatives pricing
- asset allocation
- trading strategies
- capital requirements

This project investigates whether more advanced volatility models provide better forecasting and risk estimation compared to simpler benchmarks.

The workflow follows a realistic quantitative research pipeline:


Market Data
|
v
Returns Calculation
|
v
Volatility Modelling
|
+----------------+
| |
Historical EWMA
Volatility Volatility
|
|
GARCH(1,1)
|
v
Forecast Evaluation
|
v
Risk Analytics
|
+----------------+
| |
Historical VaR Parametric VaR
|
GARCH-based VaR
|
v
VaR Backtesting
|
v
Streamlit Dashboard


---

